## Context
Reviewer 2 asked for the CDM passage in §2.2 to show how the mechanism actually
worked and how carbon accounting travelled from it into the wider field, rather
than asserting the migration. Tracker: 0141.

## Relevant passages
- `content/manuscript.qmd` §2.2 — CDM functioning; "concept later migrated";
  "carbon accounting not financial accounting"; post-2012 demand.

## Actions
1. Describe CDM functioning concretely: the CER unit, the additionality test, the
   project cycle, named actors.
2. Give examples for "the concept later migrated" — where the accounting logic
   reappeared.
3. Substantiate "carbon accounting not financial accounting": what the distinction
   does and why it matters here.
4. Name who generated post-2012 demand once the first commitment period lapsed.

## Test (prose ratchet)
- Negative guard only: no new define-by-negation / em-dash breach in §2.2
  (`tests/test_manuscript_prose.py`).

